!! Widget: `<$present>`

|!Attribute |!Default |!Purpose |
|`slides` |(required) |Filter expression yielding ordered slide-tiddler titles. Evaluated in the widget's context, so variables set above the widget are visible. |
|`section-field` |`mm.slide-of` |Field whose value groups slides into sections (the horizontal nav axis). Slides without a value bucket individually. |
|`layout-field` |`mm.slide-layout` |Field naming the layout template (resolved as `$:/plugins/rimir/present/layouts/<name>`). Missing/blank/unknown ‚Üí `default`. |
|`caption-field` |`caption` |Field used to label slides in the HUD and breadcrumb. Falls back to the leaf segment of the tiddler title. |
|`notes-field` |`mm.slide-notes` |Field carrying presenter notes (shown in the N overlay). |
|`title` |empty |Display label for the deck ‚Äî appears in the top-left of the overlay. |
|`start-section` |`0` |Zero-based section index to open on. |
|`start-slide` |`0` |Zero-based slide index within the starting section. |
|`on-close-actions` |empty |Wikitext actions invoked when the user closes the overlay. Typical use: clear a state tiddler that gated `$reveal`. |

!! Keyboard

|!Key |!Effect |
|`‚Üê` `‚Üí` |Move between sections. Within a deep-dive view, no-op (use Esc / breadcrumb). |
|`‚Üë` `‚Üì` |Move between slides within the current section. |
|`Space` |Linear advance ‚Äî down within section, then jump to next section's top slide. |
|`Backspace` |Linear reverse. |
|`Home` / `End` |Jump to first / last slide. Clears any deep-dive stack. |
|`N` |Toggle the presenter-notes panel. |
|`?` (or `/`) |Toggle the keyboard cheat sheet. |
|`Esc` |Pop one stack level if deep-dived; close help/notes overlays if open; otherwise close the deck. |

Set `$:/config/rimir/present/no-esc-close` to `yes` to disable the global Esc handler (e.g. when embedding inside another modal).

!! Layout tiddlers

Layouts live under `$:/plugins/rimir/present/layouts/<name>`. The widget transcludes the chosen layout with `currentTiddler` bound to the slide, so you can read the slide's fields directly:

|!Layout |!Slide fields read |
|`default` |`caption`, body text |
|`title` |`caption` (large), body (subtitle) |
|`two-column` |`caption`, `mm.slide-left`, `mm.slide-right`, body |
|`quote` |body (the quote), `caption` or `mm.slide-attribution` (attribution) |
|`image` |`mm.slide-image` (src), `caption`, body |
|`full` |body ‚Äî no chrome |

!! Filter operator (in rimir/mindmap)

|!Operator |!Input |!Output |
|`[<pres>mm-presentation-slides[]]` |presentation tiddler titles |Flat ordered slide titles: for each input presentation, walks its `mm.slides-order` and concatenates each owner's slide tiddlers in `mm.slide-order` order. Owners that don't exist or have no slides are silently skipped. |

The mindmap plugin wires this filter to `$present`'s `slides=` via the page-template tiddler `$:/plugins/rimir/mindmap/templates/present-overlay`.

!! State tiddlers

|!Tiddler |!Purpose |!Set by |
|`$:/state/rimir/mindmap/present-target` |Title of the presentation tiddler to play |Play buttons (header + modebar ‚ñ∂), Shift+F2 hotkey |
|`$:/state/rimir/mindmap/present-open` |`yes` while overlay is open |Play button + Esc/√ó close action |
|`$:/config/rimir/present/no-esc-close` |`yes` to disable global Esc handler |User config |

